    "body": "Following up from our discussion on Gitter, I think we should ditch the `ValidatorInductor` struct and just go with a simple function, much like the `process_deposit()` fn in the spec.\r\n\r\nI think the function should have the following signature:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\npub fn process_deposit(\r\n    state: &mut BeaconState,\r\n    deposit: &Deposit\r\n    spec: &ChainSpec)\r\n-> Result<usize, Error> \r\n```\r\n\r\nWhere the returned `usize` is the index of the new/updated validator in `BeaconState.validator_registry`.\r\n\r\nThe `Deposit` struct is not presently in the code base, however it is included in a PR I'm working on presently. I _should_ be able to get that in this afternoon, but the Rust meetup is this evening so it'll be tomorrow morning at the latest.\r\n\r\nIt's likely that I missed something in this fn signature, if something seems wrong it probably is :)\r\n\r\nI hope this helps. As always, don't hesitate to ask questions :)",
